    "title": "Man charged for the murder of his wife",
    "text": "By Austin Simms ,\n1 hour ago MORGANTOWN, WV (LOOTPRESS) – A West Virginia man has been arrested for the murder of his wife.\nAccording to the Monongalia County Sheriff’s Office, on April 25, 2024, Rick Allen Cordes, age 49 of Morgantown, was charged with first degree murder for the death of his wife Jennifer L. Hribar, 39 of Morgantown.\nCordes was arraigned in front of Magistrate Nabors no bond is set at this time.\nAnyone with information is asked to call the Monongalia County Sheriff’s Office at 304-291-7260.\nThis is an ongoing investigation, and no additional information will be released at this time, according to police.\nOriginal story:\nAccording to the Monongalia County Sheriff’s Office, on Friday, April 19, 2024, at approximately 8:30 p.m., Monongalia County Sheriff’s Office Deputies were dispatched to a shooting on Falling Water Lane.\nUpon arriving on scene, Deputies located a female victim with an apparent fatal gunshot wound. The female was pronounced dead at the scene. Monongalia County Sheriff’s Detectives responded to the scene to investigate.\nMon EMS, Brookhaven Fire Department and Cheat Lake Fire Department responded to the scene to assist with the emergency response.\nExpand All Read in NewsBreak",
